text.tspan: Rate of deaths attributed to unsafe sanitation vs. GDP per capita, 2019
The estimated annual number of deaths attributed to unsafe sanitation per 100,000 individuals. Gross domestic
product (GDP) per capita is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019); Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
Note: To allow comparisons between countries and over time the death rate from unsafe sanitation metric is age-standardized. The GDP per
capita is expressed in international-$ at 2017 prices.
